║  NO-BREAKJOINTS CBRING v12 — CODE-REVIEW PATCH (29 findings)               ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

 New in v12 (all findings from v11 code review):

   BUG-1  _suppress/_restore cached-list pair
          getconnections was called twice per signal per frame.  Each pair
          now shares one connection list captured at suppress-time and
          reused verbatim at restore-time.  Eliminates double-query race
          and halves the number of getconnections calls per drag.

   BUG-2  lerpCompleted flag gates FireServer
          The remote no longer fires when the lerp loop was broken early
          (torso destroyed mid-drag).  A boolean set only on clean loop
          completion guards the FireServer/InvokeServer branch.

   BUG-3  Kill handler disconnects all 4 persistent signals
          Players.PlayerAdded, Players.PlayerRemoving,
          LocalPlayer.CharacterAdded, and LocalPlayer.Team are now stored
          in the Connections table and torn down by the kill handler.

   BUG-4  WireCharacter disconnects stale CharacterAdded connection
          Before overwriting CharAddedConns[uid], the existing connection
          is disconnected.  Prevents doubled OnChar invocations from a
          race between the initial GetPlayers loop and PlayerAdded.

   BUG-5  localCharConns cleared on each respawn
          OnChar now disconnects and clears the previous character's
          connections before wiring the new one.  Prevents unbounded
          growth across many respawns.

   BUG-6  Stale currentRemote revalidated each frame
          The Heartbeat checks currentRemote.Parent before the FindRemote
          branch.  A destroyed remote resets currentRemote to nil and
          triggers a fresh search.

   EDGE-1 BuildArcVis commits pool only after full build
          ArcPool = nxt is written only when all 2+ARC_SEGS parts are
          confirmed.  UpdateArcVis also guards against a partial pool.

   EDGE-2 FetchWhitelist retry loop respects ScriptKilled
          Each iteration checks CFG.ScriptKilled before the wait and
          before the HttpGet, preventing a woken coroutine from
          overwriting a post-kill scrubbed Whitelist.

   EDGE-3 GetArcFolder validates Parent == workspace
          Previously accepted a folder re-parented to any service.  Now
          requires Parent == workspace.

   EDGE-4 AncestryChanged nils _rebindUIRef
          Prevents task.delay callbacks from writing .TextColor3/.Color
          to dead UI instances after an external CoreGui sweep.

   EDGE-5 Dropdown pre-computes display:lower()
          displayLow is cached per row in BuildRowCache.  FilterRows no
          longer allocates a lowercased string per row per keystroke.

   EDGE-6 FetchWhitelist validates URL format
          Rejects non-http(s) URLs before calling HttpGet.

   EDGE-7 RebuildArcAngles guards AngleCap == 0
          Clamps the half-angle to a minimum of 1° to prevent a
          degenerate single-line arc.

   PERF-A RootCache eliminates per-frame HRP child search
          OnChar caches HumanoidRootPart in RootCache[LocalPlayer].
          The Heartbeat reads from the cache instead of FindFirstChild.

   PERF-B LerpFrames snapshotted before lerp loop
          CFG.LerpFrames is read once through the proxy metamethod
          before the loop rather than on every iteration.

   PERF-C display:lower() pre-computed — covered by EDGE-5.

   PERF-D DD_ROW_TWEEN module-level constant
          TweenInfo.new(0.08) is no longer allocated per hover event.

   PERF-E SetBeam skips redundant Size write
          A weak per-part cache stores last len+thick.  The Size
          property is only written when the value changes by > 0.005.
          CFrame.lookAt Vector3 midpoint allocation also eliminated by
          computing all six components inline.

   PERF-F ARC_TOTAL constant
          2 + ARC_SEGS is precomputed as ARC_TOTAL.

   PERF-G _randBuf reuses a module-level table
          RandName no longer allocates a table.create(6) on every call.

   REL-1  BuildGUI wrapped in pcall
          Hard crashes from denied CoreGui access are caught and logged;
          the combat logic and keybind connections are registered
          regardless of GUI availability.

   REL-2  Kill handler pair/ipairs audit (documented, correct as-is)
          PlayerTeamConns and CharAddedConns are UserId-keyed hash
          tables → pairs correct.  localCharConns is an integer array
          → ipairs correct.

   REL-3  GUI tweens cancelled before ScreenGui:Destroy
          MkToggle registers a canceller callback in _guiTweenCancellers.
          BuildGUI and the kill handler call CancelGUITweens() before
          destroying the ScreenGui, preventing tween callbacks from
          firing on destroyed instances.

   REL-4  WireCharacter retry cache writes wrapped in pcall
          Defensive against a mid-stream character reset that destroys
          the char reference between the 0.5 s delay and the write.

   REL-5  DragAndFire drag-error warn removed in non-debug builds
          The warn that exposed internal line numbers is now guarded by
          CFG.Debug (default false).

   MAINT-1 triggerRowDimRefs unified with _rebindUIRef
           Both variables now reference the same table.

   MAINT-2 guiVisible removed
           Dead flag that was never read.

   MAINT-3 "NoCBring Config" label uses _S.Title
           Consistent with the EV-4 policy.

   MAINT-4 FetchWhitelist retry restructured for clarity
           Kill-guard extracted to top of each iteration; wait moved to
           a cleaner position.

